alerts.message:
...Snow for the afternoon commute...

Snow will continue over the southern Adirondacks...Lake George
Saratoga region...southern Vermont...the Berkshires northern
Taconics and the greater capital region between 3 and 5 PM. A
transition to sleet and plain rain is expected for the capital
region towards 5 PM, and some spotty freezing rain may be possible
over the higher elevations, where temperatures are near the
freezing mark. Additional snowfall will range from a half an inch
in the valleys on the untreated surfaces to 2 inches over the
southern Adirondacks. Visibilities will lower to a half mile in
the snow occasionally. Temperatures will continue to rise into the
mid and upper 30s by the late afternoon. Untreated roadways maybe
slippery so use caution while driving.


Taw

257 PM EDT Thu Oct 27 2016
